In large saucepan over medium-high heat, melt margarine. Add chicken and garlic; saute 3 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink inside. Slowly stir in 1-2/3 cups water, rice mix and Special Seasonings; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until white rice is tender. Stir in dressing; let cool 10 minutes. Arrange lettuce on serving platter. Top with rice mixture. Sprinkle with cheese and croutons, if desired.